<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,410]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,271,151,177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Species assigned 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loeblich and Tappan" authorityYear="1984" box="[490,638,152,177]" class="Nodosariata" family="Reophacidae" genus="Leptohalysis" kingdom="Chromista" order="Hormosinina" pageId="2" pageNumber="25" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[490,638,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">Leptohalysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with minute test (&lt;130 µm long, ~20 µm wide), comprising more or less linear series of chambers, increasing slightly but regularly in size to give elongate, gently tapered form. Chambers globular, abutting with only slight overlap. Wall finely agglutinated, mainly comprising grains with flat exposed faces that abut to create outer surface resembling uneven pavement; edges of grains obscured by copious amounts of organic cement.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
